        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 11:22PM MDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 1122 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Lamar, or 13 miles west of Imperial, moving south
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Champion, Crete, and Church Grove Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
